Title: LONG TEMPO EFFORTS
WorkoutDescription: FOCUS ON STEADY SPIN IN THE 150-160 RANGE FOR 10-30 MINUTE PERIODS - STEADY EASIER SPINNING BETWEEN EFFORTS - Warm up and ride into the 130HR ranges, add a few jumps, get the system going - Check your bio feedback here. When warmed up and ready, choose sections of trail or roads, especially on the hill grades and climbs, and spin mainly seated into the 150-160HR ranges for duration s of 10-20 plus minutes - Power goal can be 240 - 260 PLUS watts, just keep HR under 165 - If you feel good and can work up to 30 min efforts, go for it - Easier, steady spin for between all efforts today, 130-140's HR - Work efforts on and off all day until speed and power drops - If speed or power doesn't drop, work these all day and have fun with it - Remember, push speed and power, keep breath deep and HR in line
CoachComments: BE FLUID - KEEP HR IN LINE, PUSH POWER IF FEELING GOOD
AthleteComments: *01/01/2023 Abigail Snyder: Legs felt good. Called for a ride because I was near hypothermia from the rain and cold.*

Title: SEATED TO STANDING FORCE INTO TEMPO
WorkoutDescription: GET INTO SEATED FORCE EFFORTS ON CLIMBS, FINISHING THE EFFORT STANDING - WORK SOME TEMPO BETWEEN A FEW EFFORTS - Warm up into the 130's HR, check how you feel - When ready, on a climb, shift a gear or two harder (or use a single speed) remain seated and grind a 20-30 second effort, then stand and continue that effort for another 20-30 seconds - Efforts can be shorter 30-60 seconds or longer 2-5 plus minute efforts, just work the seated to standing theme - HR can rise into the 160's-170's, Power 300-500 watt range - cadence 50-70 rpm but focus more on grinding an effort - Sit and spin into tempo ranges, 150-160HR between a few efforts today, otherwise spin easier, 140's, to recover.
CoachComments: 60-90 MIN INSIDE - IF OUTDOORS DOESN'T NEED TO BE THIS PERFECT, JUST WORK FORCE, HILLS, SOME TEMPO - TIME TO BUILD STRENGTH
AthleteComments: *01/02/2023 Abigail Snyder: Absolutely shattered. Found myself pushing through an effort just to collapse on the saddle for a brief moment to recover. Oof.*

Title: EverAthlete: RideStrong Stability
AthleteComments: *01/04/2023 Abigail Snyder: Skipped the gym today as stomach is definitely still off, and fatigue is high.*

Title: EASY SPIN / SINGLE LEG DRILLS
WorkoutDescription: KEEP IT EASY TODAY AND SPIN IN THE 130-150HR RANGE KEEP IT EASY AND LIGHT AND WORK WITH A NATURAL CADENCE ---- keep today to a steady spin in the 130-150 ranges where you feel comfortable spinning. No need to push it today.Try to keep 130 as a minimum HR range to maintain. On flats/hills, un-clip at times and spin one leg for 30 seconds, switch legs then back to easy spin - Add these when appropriate, on safe terrain, away from autos.
CoachComments: EASY 60 MINUTES - TAKE IT EASY, SAVE IT FOR THE REST OF THE WEEK
AthleteComments: *01/04/2023 Abigail Snyder: Kept it easy, but definitely noticed the fatigue. Legs just felt heavy and tired… and body felt fatigued, though as likely from some stomach bug/food poisoning all day as anything else.*

Title: EverAthlete: Core
WorkoutDescription: Complete Ride Strong Strength Cycle A weekly core session.

Title: STEADY ENDURANCE
WorkoutDescription: STEADY PACE IN THE 140-155 RANGES MAINLY WITH FEW BREAKS - WORK WITH A SLIGHTLY FASTER CADENCE THE WHOLE TIME TODAY - Warm up and ride into the 130-140 ranges. Check your bio feedback here. Where is your breath? Where is your PE? How do your legs feel? If you feel good fatigue, add more warm up and back off the ranges for the day- If you feel good then spin in the 140-155 range for most of the ride today - Spin seated with a slightly faster cadence today, all day long - Add easier spin breaks when needed - If normal cadence is in the 85RPM range, aim for 90 plus on longer segments
CoachComments: FLUID SPIN, CAN BE LONGER, JUST GO FOR IT - TAP ON THE PEDALS, KEEP IT FUN
AthleteComments: *01/04/2023 Abigail Snyder: Felt pretty ok. Stomach is still a little off, so there’s some fatigue from that I think, but otherwise warmed up and felt decent.*

Title: SHORT SUB LT SPIN EFFORTS
WorkoutDescription: WORK WITH A FASTER CADENCE SEATED, WHILE REACHING THE TARGETED HR RANGES TODAY - TRY TO WORK WITH LESS FORCE AND MORE SPIN - take your time warming up as always. Ease into the 130 HR range and check your bio feedback - When you are feeling good, up your pace into tempo for 3-5 minutes, 150-160HR, then stay seated and spin with a faster cadence into the Sub LT range, 160-170 HR range - 260-280 PLUS watts - Try to hold that effort for at least 3-5 minutes, up to 7-10 minutes if feeling good on a climb - Keep it as simple as that and work in 5-10 efforts today - Keep the rest of the day an easier/steady spin in the 130-140'sHR ranges
CoachComments: PICK SHORT HILLS AND SPIN THEM SEATED, SUB LT RANGES - IF PE IS HIGH TODAY, LEGS HURT, JUST BACK OFF THE EFFORTS AND SPIN IT OUT - FLIP SIDE IF ALL IS GOOD AND YOU CAN WORK MORE POWER GO FOR IT, JUST KEEP HR IN LINE
AthleteComments: *01/06/2023 Abigail Snyder: Felt pretty decent. Cold. Didn't dress quite warm enough.*

Title: SHORT SPRINTS - STEADY SPIN
WorkoutDescription: STEADY SPIN IN THE 140-155HR RANGES MAINLY WITH FEW BREAKS - FOCUS ON WORKING SMOOTH AND WITH A NATURAL CADENCE - Warm up and ride into the 130-140 ranges. Check your bio feedback here. If you feel good fatigue, add more warm up and back off the ranges for the day- Once fluid spin in the 145-155HR range for most of the day - Add easier spin breaks when needed - Toss in a handful of 10-20 second all out sprints through the day. Keep it simple today.
CoachComments: ADD SHORT EFFORTS RANDOMLY IF OUTSIDE - IF THE LEGS HURT, BAG THE SHORT EFFORTS AND STEADY SPIN IT FOR THE DAY
AthleteComments: *01/05/2023 Abigail Snyder: Switching ride/rest day because we have dinner plans on Saturday that would mean I'd need to get up at 4 a.m in order to get 2.5 hours in before work... and I'd really rather just ride in the daylight when I get off work at 4:30 p.m. on Friday... and enjoy Saturday with friends.* *01/07/2023 Abigail Snyder: Legs felt dull. No snap. Crashed and banged up knee… went from putting an effort in to surviving.*

Title: FORCE EFFORTS EARLY - MODERATE FAST PACE EFFORTS TO END
WorkoutDescription: WORK INTO HILLS AND GRIND OUT SEATED/STANDING FORCE EFFORTS EARLY RIDE, THEN FOCUS ON FAST PACED EFFORT IN THE SUB LT/LT RANGE TO END - Warm up into the 140's HR, check how you feel - When ready, early ride, shift a gear or two harder (or use a single speed) Work both standing and seated and grind a few hills - Seek out any incline or hill, can be shorter 30-60 seconds or longer 1-3 plus minute efforts - HR can rise into the 160-170's, cadence 50-70 rpm - power goal 300-500 watts - Work a handful of force efforts first half of the ride, 4-8 efforts - Second half of the ride get into race pace efforts, aim for longer 5-10 minute sustained efforts - HR can rise anywhere in the 160-175 HR range, Power goal anywhere from 260-310 watts - Focus more on a fast paced effort and bike handling than the numbers but use the numbers to guide you - Keep plenty of easier spin between efforts today
CoachComments: A COMBO OF FORCE AND SPEED AT THE END, HAVE FUN WITH IT - INDOORS 60-90 MIN
AthleteComments: *01/09/2023 Abigail Snyder: Felt pretty broken at the start, but eased into it. Really struggled to get into SubLT range on the second half... felt like I was pushing hard, but had no real response.*

Title: TEMPO ON CLIMBS/FEW SPRINTS TO END
WorkoutDescription: GOAL IS TO WORK IN A STEADY FLOW, HR IN THE 150-160 RANGES, WITH FEWER BREAKS - SPIN SMOOTH AND WITH A NATURAL, SLIGHTLY FASTER CADENCE - ON CLIMBS, HOLD TEMPO RANGES BUT KEEP IT THERE - Warm up into the 140's HR and check bio feedback as always, if feeling greater fatigue, higher PE, add more warm up - When feeling good, get into a steady fluid endurance pace today in the 140-155HR ranges - Keep breath deep and tap on the pedals - On all climbs, tempo spin it, 150-160 HR range, as much speed and power but cap HR at 165 - Keep it this simple all day, with fewer breaks. - END OF RIDE, WORK IN 2-3 30-40 SECOND SPRINTS, RAMPING UP TO ALL OUT IN THE LAST 10 SECONDS OF THE SPRINT - If outdoors spring in safe places!
CoachComments: GET THE LEGS SPINNING FLUID, FEW SPRINTS - KEEP IT SIMPLE TODAY

Title: MID RIDE LONG TEMPO/FEW SPRINTS TO END
WorkoutDescription: WARM UP WELL TODAY, WORK A FEW TEMPO EFFORTS MID RIDE AND THEN END WITH A FEW FAST PACED EFFORTS/SPRINTS - Warm up into the 130-140's HR, check how you feel - Then ease into a steady pace, 140-150's HR for first third of the day or longer - Mid ride, work a few tempo efforts, 10-20 plus minutes, 150-160HR ranges, 280-310 watts - Then get back into steady paced spinning and in the last 10-15 minutes of the day, work into a few 30-60 second fast paced efforts/sprints - 300-600 watts, just nuke it, easy spin to recover then another.
CoachComments: GET THE LEGS SPINNING FLUID, FEW SPRINTS ALL YOU NEED

Title: THRESHOLD EARLY - LONG TEMPO TO END
WorkoutDescription: WORK INTO SHORT AND LONG THRESHOLD EFFORTS TODAY - KEEP IT SIMPLE AND WORK HARD EFFORTS ALL DAY - END THE DAY WITH ONE LONGER STEADY TEMPO EFFORT - take your time warming up as always. Ease into the 130 HR range and check your bio feedback - If you have any fatigue today while warming up, add more warm up spin before efforts - Then choose stretches of road or trail for an effort, stay seated, spin into tempo ranges first, 150-160HR range for 3-4 minutes, then up it into threshold, 165-175 HR range - Try to hold that effort for at least 5-7 minutes at times and at times shorter 1-2 min efforts are good - if feeling good, hold it up to 10 minutes - Power goals can be 280-310 plus watts for efforts - Space efforts today with steady spin in the 130's-140's HR and aim to get in 4-6 good efforts - End of ride, a 10-20 min fluid tempo effort, HR 150-160
CoachComments: RAMP UP TO SOME THRESHOLD EFFORTS TODAY EARLY RIDE - JUST WORK THE EFFORT DON'T STRESS ON POWER EITHER WAY
AthleteComments: *01/21/2023 Abigail Snyder: Short on time and low on heart rate zones. Rode with a couple of friends, because this loop is pretty far out, and I don’t like riding it solo, especially when it’s cold out. Couldn’t stick with them and push all the way into threshold most of the day. Finished early, but feet were completely frozen, so decided to call it rather than going out for another loop solo. 100% an awesome day on the bike, even if it didn’t really accomplish workout goals.*

Title: SEATED FORCE AND SPRINTS
WorkoutDescription: FIRST HALF OF THE DAY WORK SEATED FORCE EFFORTS INTERMIXED WITH SHORT SPRINTS - END THE DAY WITH FLUID TEMPO EFFORTS - Warm up as always checking bio feedback, taking your time getting fluid in the 140's HR - Seek out short to moderate hills, 1-5 minutes in length, shift to a slightly harder gear, RPM's in the 50-70 range, STAY seated, and grind out a seated force effort, increasing the intensity from easier at the start to a hard force effort at the end, 30-60 seconds up to 5 min effort if on a longer hill - 300-500 watts - Spin steady after the force effort and then next effort work 3-5 short sprints, 10-20 second sprints mixed with easier spin - Then steady spin and do another seated force effort - Work this mix between seated force and sprints first half of the ride - Second half of the ride get into a mix of short and longer tempo efforts, working as much speed and power but keeping HR in the 150-160 range, 165 max - Space everything today with easier and steady spin, anywhere in the 140-150's HR.
CoachComments: SEATED FORCE BUILDS STRENGTH, TEMPO BUILDS ENDURANCE
AthleteComments: *01/23/2023 Abigail Snyder: Exhausted. Really had to push at the end. Cold and WINDY, so mentally a push in addition to the physical effort. I’m so sick of being cold….*

Title: THRESHOLD EARLY - TEMPO/SUB LT TO FINISH
WorkoutDescription: WORK 3-5 MIN THRESHOLD EFFORTS FIRST HALF OF THE RIDE - SECOND HALF RIDE BETWEEN TEMPO AND SUB LT RANGES - Warm up into the 130's, check how you feel - Once fluid and ready for an effort, spin seated into tempo for a few minutes and then nuke it into a shorter 3-5 min threshold effort - Fluid cadence, shift down, work harder - HR can rise into the 165-175 range,, but focus more on the effort over HR - Power 300 plus watts - Work 2-4 of these efforts early in the ride, - Mid ride steady spin it 140's HR, recover from the early effort - late ride work into at least one good 7-10 minute tempo effort, 150-160 HR and one good 5-7 minute sub threshold effort 160-170 HR - Power for the Sub LT - 260-280 watts - cool down and finish it out.
CoachComments: 60-90 MIN INSIDE - IF OUTDOORS DOESN'T NEED TO BE THIS PERFECT, JUST WORK IN THRESHOLD EFFORTS EARLY, FINISH WITH SUB LT/TEMPO

That first climb felt like it took everything out of me.* *02/04/2023 Abigail Snyder: I haven't been riding with power on my data screen lately, but I did feel as if, when I looked down, power seemed low in comparison to HR.*

Title: STEADY ENDURANCE - TEMPO ON CLIMBS
WorkoutDescription: GOAL IS TO WORK IN A STEADY FLOW, HR IN THE 145-160 RANGES, WITH FEWER BREAKS - SPIN SMOOTH AND WITH A NATURAL, SLIGHTLY FASTER CADENCE - ON CLIMBS, HOLD TEMPO RANGES BUT KEEP IT THERE - Warm up into the 140's HR and check bio feedback as always, if feeling greater fatigue, higher PE, add more warm up - When feeling good, get into a steady fluid endurance pace today in the 140-155HR ranges - Keep breath deep and tap on the pedals - On all climbs, tempo spin it, 150-160 HR range, as much speed and power but cap HR at 165 - Keep it this simple all day, with fewer breaks.
CoachComments: INDOORS OR OUT, GOAL IS TO WORK THIS RANGE ALL DAY ON CLIMBS, BE FLUID, KEEP IT SIMPLE

Legs were a bit tired, but heart rate response and energy seemed good. Finished out with some in-town cruising to get the time and some harder efforts in.*

Title: FUN RIDE - RIDE HOW YOU FEEL
WorkoutDescription: WORK HOWEVER YOUR FEELING TODAY - IF YOUR FEELING FATIGUED, KEEP IT EASY SPINNING AND SHORTER - IF YOUR FEELING GOOD, WORK INTO EFFORTS - KEEP PLENTY OF EASY SPINNING IN THE MIX - Always warm up into the day checking to see how your feeling in the 130-140 ranges - If your feeling good fatigue, then back of for most of the day and keep it easier spinning anywhere in the 130-150 ranges - If your feeling good, get into efforts with friends or work hard on a few hills - Work a hard race pace like day if your feeling really good for as long as you would like. Have a fun ride.
CoachComments: SHORT OR LONG, HARD OR EASY, GROUP RIDES, SOLO, ETC, JUST HAVE A FUN DAY - IF YOU FEEL GOOD MAYBE WORK SOME TEMPO ALL DAY OR SUB LT OR RANDOMLY RIDE! IF TIRED KEEP TODAY EASIER

Title: SEATED TO STANDING FORCE INTO TEMPO
WorkoutDescription: GET INTO SEATED FORCE EFFORTS ON CLIMBS, FINISHING THE EFFORT STANDING - WORK SOME TEMPO BETWEEN A FEW EFFORTS - Warm up into the 130's HR, check how you feel - When ready, on a climb, shift a gear or two harder (or use a single speed) remain seated and grind a 20-30 second effort, then stand and continue that effort for another 20-30 seconds - Efforts can be shorter 30-60 seconds or longer 2-5 plus minute efforts, just work the seated to standing theme - HR can rise into the 160's-170's, Power 400-500 watt range - cadence 50-70 rpm but focus more on grinding an effort - Sit and spin into tempo ranges, 150-160HR between a few efforts today, otherwise spin easier, 140's, to recover.
CoachComments: IF OUTDOORS DOESN'T NEED TO BE THIS PERFECT, JUST WORK FORCE, HILLS, SOME TEMPO - BUILD SOME STRENGTH

Title: MID RIDE THRESHOLD - CAPPED WITH TEMPO EFFORTS
WorkoutDescription: WORK INTO SHORT AND LONG THRESHOLD EFFORTS TODAY MID RIDE - KEEP IT SIMPLE - CAP THE DAY WITH TEMPO EFFORTS - take your time warming up as always. Ease into the 130 HR range and check your bio feedback - If you have any fatigue today while warming up, add more warm up spin before efforts - To start the day, spin into tempo efforts, one longer 10 plus minute or shorter efforts if outside, HR 150-160, power 270 plus watts - Steady spin for a little then nuke some harder threshold efforts mid ride - Choose stretches of road or trail for an effort, seated and standing, spin it into threshold ranges, 165-175 HR range - Short or longer efforts, from a minute to 5 plus minutes - Power goals can be 280-310 plus watts for efforts - End of ride, work more tempo, short and long efforts or one longer effort 10 plus minutes
CoachComments: RAMP UP TO SOME THRESHOLD EFFORTS TODAY MID RIDE - JUST WORK THE EFFORT EVEN IF PE IS HIGH AND HR IS ON THE LOWER END!

Title: SUB LT SPIN EFFORTS
WorkoutDescription: WORK WITH A FASTER CADENCE SEATED, WHILE REACHING THE TARGETED HR RANGES TODAY - TRY TO WORK WITH LESS FORCE AND MORE SPIN - take your time warming up as always. Ease into the 130 HR range and check your bio feedback - When you are feeling good, up your pace into tempo for 3-5 minutes, 150-160HR, then stay seated and spin with a faster cadence into the Sub LT range, 160-170 HR range - 265-290 plus watts - Try to hold that effort for at least 3-5 minutes, up to 10 minutes - Keep it as simple as that and work in 5-10 efforts today - Keep the rest of the day an easier/steady spin in the 130-140'sHR ranges
CoachComments: PICK SHORT HILLS AND SPIN THEM SEATED, SUB LT RANGES - IF PE IS HIGH TODAY, LEGS HURT, JUST BACK OFF THE EFFORTS AND SPIN IT OUT

Legs were still sore, but overall my mood improved as I finish out the last two hours.* *02/18/2023 Abigail Snyder: Also, my power meter died when my bike fell in the FREEZING Creek… Or before, but I noticed it afterwards. Annoying.*

Title: LONG TEMPO EFFORTS
WorkoutDescription: FOCUS ON STEADY SPIN IN THE 150-160 RANGE FOR 20-30 MINUTE PERIODS - STEADY EASIER SPINNING BETWEEN EFFORTS - Warm up and ride into the 130 ranges, add a few jumps, get the system going - Check your bio feedback here. When warmed up and ready, choose sections of trail or roads, especially on the hill grades and climbs, and spin mainly seated into the 150-160HR ranges for duration s of 10-20 plus minutes - Power goal can be 240 - 270 PLUS watts, just keep HR under 165 - If you feel good and can work up to 30 min efforts, go for it - Easier, steady spin for between all efforts today, 130-140's HR - Work efforts on and off all day until speed and power drops - If speed or power doesn't drop, work these all day and have fun with it - Remember, push speed and power, keep breath deep and HR in line
CoachComments: INDOORS OR OUT, GOAL IS TO WORK THIS RANGE ALL DAY, BE FLUID, HAVE FUN, KEEP IT SIMPLE TODAY

Title: JUMPS WITH TEMPO
WorkoutDescription: WORK INTO SHORT SPRINT/JUMPS, FROM SEATED TO STANDING FOLLOWED WITH TEMPO SPIN - Warm up as usual in the 130-140's, if you need more warm up, take it - Then on flats or hills, get into a round a jumps, Start seated, then NUKE it to a standing sprint for 2-3 seconds, then sit and jump/sprint again - Repeat for 3-6 jumps in a row - Don't worry about HR, just work powerful sprints/jumps - Immediately following the jumps, sit and spin into tempo ranges, 150-160 HR for 7-10 plus minutes - You can use power to challenge the range, 260-290 watts but cap HR at 165 - Aim for at least 3-4 of these sessions today - easier/steady fun spin between
CoachComments: GET INTO A MIX OF EFFORTS - NUKE IT FOR THE SHORT EFFORTS, INTO TEMPO, LIKE YOUR CHASING DOWN A FRIEND ON A RIDE!

Title: TEMPO INTO SHORT RACE PACE EFFORTS
WorkoutDescription: STEADY SPIN IT WITH SOME SPEED INTO SHORT RACE PACE EFFORTS TODAY - KEEP LOTS OF EASIER SPIN IN THE MIX - Warm up as always checking how you feel, adding more warm up if needed - Then when ready, get into a steady fluid/tempo spin, 145-160 HR ranges, for 2-3 minutes or until feeling fluid - Once in a fluid pace, NUKE it into a fast race pace effort for 30-60 seconds, like you are trying to gap a rider ahead of you - HR can rise into the 160-170's, but focus on the effort more than HR - Fully recover after these little sessions today for 5-10 minutes spinning easy and fluid - Work a handful of these efforts, 5-10 efforts, group a few close together, space a few apart, depending on how you feel. - Anytime in the ride, add 5-10 minutes of tempo spin, 150-160HR
CoachComments: WORK IN SOME EFFORTS, PREP THE LEGS FOR THIS WEEKEND - ON THE BIKE FOR THIS WEEKEND AS WELL

Title: SHORT SPIN - PREP
WorkoutDescription: KEEP IT EASY TODAY AND SPIN IN THE 135-155 RANGE FOR MOST OF THE SPIN - KEEP IT LIGHT ON THE PEDALS AND WORK WITH A NATURAL CADENCE - ADD A FEW VERY SHORT 6-10 SEC BURSTS TODAY AS WELL - Warm up and check to see how your feeling once you spin into the 140 HR range today. How is your breathing here? How do your legs feel? --- keep most of the spin in the 140-150HR ranges but when your feeling it, add a few short 6-10 sec standing or seated bursts of speed working super hard with fast leg speed - Completely recover after each effort for 7-10 min and spin easy - only perform a few efforts (2-3) and then spin it home easy
CoachComments: FEW EFFORTS - MAINLY FLUID AND EASY

Title: FORCE EFFORTS EARLY - MODERATE FAST PACE EFFORTS TO END
WorkoutDescription: WORK INTO HILLS AND GRIND OUT SEATED/STANDING FORCE EFFORTS EARLY RIDE, THEN FOCUS ON FAST PACED EFFORT IN THE SUB LT/LT RANGE TO END - Warm up into the 140's HR, check how you feel - When ready, early ride, shift a gear or two harder (or use a single speed) Work both standing and seated and grind a few hills - Seek out any incline or hill, can be shorter 30-60 seconds or longer 1-3 plus minute efforts - HR can rise into the 160-170's, cadence 50-70 rpm - power goal 300-500 watts - Work a handful of force efforts first half of the ride, 4-8 efforts - Second half of the ride get into race pace efforts, aim for longer 5-10 minute sustained efforts - HR can rise anywhere in the 160-175 HR range, Power goal anywhere from 260-320 watts - Focus more on a fast paced effort and bike handling than the numbers but use the numbers to guide you - Keep plenty of easier spin between efforts today
CoachComments: A COMBO OF FORCE AND SPEED AT THE END, HAVE FUN WITH IT - INDOORS 60-90 MIN

Title: STOMP THEN SPIN
WorkoutDescription: START EFFORTS WITH BIG GEARS, ON STEEPS, ETC, GRINDING THE FIRST 10-15 SECONDS, THEN SIT, SHIFT AND SPIN FAST LEGS TO FINISH - STEADY TEMPO BETWEEN - After warm up, and feeling fluid, seek out hills and work into efforts starting with a slower cadence, harder gears and NUKE it for the first 10-15 seconds - Could come to a slow roll into a hill with big gears and start from there, then after the initial grind, sit and shift up a gear easier, spinning with a fast and fluid cadence while maintaining Sub LT HR in the 160-170 ranges, for an additional 3-5 minutes - power 260-290 watt ranges - Work in 4-6 of these efforts today - Between efforts spin steady/ tempo ranges, anywhere in the 140-160 HR, fluid - End of ride, 1-2 form sprints, big gears, seated fast spin 10 seconds
CoachComments: GRIND OUT THE START OF EFFORTS, THEN SIT AND SPIN IT OUT - MIX OF FORCE AND SPIN, GOOD FUNCTIONAL POWER BUILDERS

Title: THRESHOLD EFFORTS - HAMMER RIDE
WorkoutDescription: WORK INTO SHORT AND LONG THRESHOLD EFFORTS TODAY - KEEP IT SIMPLE AND WORK HARD EFFORTS ALL DAY - take your time warming up as always. Ease into the 130 HR range and check your bio feedback - If you have any fatigue today while warming up, add more warm up spin before efforts - Then choose stretches of road or trail for an effort, stay seated, spin into tempo ranges first, 150-160HR range for 3-4 minutes, then up it into threshold, 165-175 HR range - Try to hold that effort for at least 4-5 minutes at times and at times shorter 1-2 min efforts are good - if feeling good, hold it up to 10 minutes - Power goals can be 290-320 plus watts for efforts - Space efforts today with steady spin in the 130's-140's HR and aim to get in 4-6 good efforts - End of ride, 1-2 big gear form sprints, big ring super fast cadence seated on a flat or slight downgrade for 10-15 seconds
CoachComments: GO HAMMER - WORK ALL THE CLIMBS TODAY - TIME TO GET THE LEGS FIRED UP - RAMP INTO EFFORTS TOO - IF THEY FEEL DEAD, THEN DO A FEW EFFORTS, BACK OFF MOST OF THE RIDE

Title: TEMPO INTO SHORT RACE PACE EFFORTS
WorkoutDescription: STEADY SPIN IT WITH SOME SPEED INTO SHORT RACE PACE EFFORTS TODAY - KEEP LOTS OF EASIER SPIN IN THE MIX - Warm up as always checking how you feel, adding more warm up if needed - Then when ready, get into a steady fluid/tempo spin, 135-150 HR ranges, for 2-3 minutes or until feeling fluid - Once in a fluid pace, NUKE it into a fast race pace effort for 30-60 seconds, like you are trying to gap a rider ahead of you - HR can rise into the 150-160's, but focus on the effort more than HR - Fully recover after these little sessions today for 5-10 minutes spinning easy and fluid - Work a handful of these efforts, 5-10 efforts, group a few close together, space a few apart, depending on how you feel. - Anytime in the ride, add 5-10 minutes of tempo spin, 140-150HR
CoachComments: WORK IN SOME EFFORTS, PREP THE LEGS FOR THIS WEEKEND - ON THE BIKE FOR THIS WEEKEND AS WELL

Title: EASY SPIN - RIDE HOW YOU FEEL
WorkoutDescription: WORK HOWEVER YOUR FEELING TODAY - IF YOUR FEELING FATIGUED, KEEP IT EASY SPINNING AND SHORTER - IF YOUR FEELING GOOD, WORK INTO EFFORTS - KEEP PLENTY OF EASY SPINNING IN THE MIX - Always warm up into the day checking to see how your feeling in the 140-150 HR ranges - If your feeling good fatigue, then back of for most of the day and keep it easier spinning anywhere in the 130-150 HR ranges - If your feeling good, get into efforts with friends or work hard on a few hills - Work a hard race pace like day if your feeling really good for as long as you would like. Have a fun ride.

Title: STEADY ENDURANCE - TEMPO ON CLIMBS
WorkoutDescription: GOAL IS TO WORK IN A STEADY FLOW, HR IN THE 145-160 RANGES, WITH FEWER BREAKS - SPIN SMOOTH AND WITH A NATURAL, SLIGHTLY FASTER CADENCE - ON CLIMBS, HOLD TEMPO RANGES BUT KEEP IT THERE - Warm up into the 140's HR and check bio feedback as always, if feeling greater fatigue, higher PE, add more warm up - When feeling good, get into a steady fluid endurance pace today in the 140-155HR ranges - Keep breath deep and tap on the pedals - On all climbs, tempo spin it, 150-160 HR range, as much speed and power but cap HR at 165 - Keep it this simple all day, with fewer breaks.
CoachComments: INDOORS OR OUT, GOAL IS TO WORK THIS RANGE ALL DAY ON CLIMBS, BE FLUID, KEEP IT SIMPLE

Title: JUMPS WITH TEMPO
WorkoutDescription: WORK INTO SHORT SPRINT/JUMPS, FROM SEATED TO STANDING FOLLOWED WITH TEMPO SPIN - Warm up as usual in the 130-140's HR ranges, if you need more warm up, take it - Then on flats or hills, get into a round a jumps, Start seated, then NUKE it to a standing sprint for 2-3 seconds, then sit and jump/sprint again - Repeat for 3-6 jumps in a row - Don't worry about HR, just work powerful sprints/jumps - Immediately following the jumps, sit and spin into tempo ranges, 150-160 HR for 7-10 plus minutes - You can use power to challenge the range, 240-270 watts but cap HR at 165 - Aim for at least 3-4 of these sessions today - easier/steady fun spin between
CoachComments: NUKE IT FOR THE SHORT EFFORTS, INTO TEMPO, LIKE YOUR CHASING DOWN A FRIEND ON A RIDE!

Title: TEMPO/SUB LT REPEATS
WorkoutDescription: START WITH A 5 MIN TEMPO EFFORT, IMMEDIATELY INCREASE INTO SUB LT RANGES FOR AN ADDITIONAL 5 MINUTES, REST FOR 5 MIN AND REPEAT - Warm up as usual into the 130's, checking how you feel - Once fluid and feeling good, spin with slightly more intensity into a tempo effort, 150-160 HR range, as much speed and power as you can, cap HR at 160 - Maintain this for 5 minutes approx, then increase intensity into the sub LT ranges - 160-170 HR range, power goal - 270-290 plus watts - Spin easy gears for about 5 minutes and repeat this once more - Steady spin it between these rounds - maybe try for 2 of these rounds today
CoachComments: DOESN'T NEED TO BE PERFECT IF OUTSIDE, JUST WORK BOTH RANGES BACK TO BACK ALL DAY

Title: ROLLING VO2 EFFORTS - SUB LT LATE
WorkoutDescription: WITH SPEED, ON SLIGHT UPHILL GRADES, ROLLERS, LONG FLATS, NUKE IT INTO A 10-30 SEC VO2 EFFORTS, SPIN THE LEGS AS FAST AS YOU CAN, STAND AND HAMMER, THEN REST - After warming up today, rode a fun steady pace in the 130-150's with fluid legs, on any terrain - First half of the ride, get to sections where your rolling at faster speeds, able to turn bigger gears with faster leg speed, Start the effort with 3-5 minutes of tempo, THEN stand and nuke it into a 10-30 second all out VO2 effort - Don't worry about HR/power, just nuke it - Power goal can be 600-700 plus watts - If you feel good you can extend the efforts up to a minute - Then sit, spin easy, recover fully and roll on until you get to more places to work these efforts - Group efforts together in a set when you can, sets of 2-4 are good - Try to work at least 5-10 plus good efforts today - Keep the spin between all efforts and sets general endurance, 140-150's HR.---END OF RIDE, ADD A FEW SUB LT - 160-170 HR, 260-290 WATTS - EFFORTS, 5-10 MINUTES - IF FEELING GOOD DO MORE
CoachComments: 60-90 MIN INSIDE - IF OUTDOORS, SEEK OUT LONGER CLIMBS AND SPIN FLUID IN THE SUB LT RANGES TODAY

Title: TIME TRIAL/HILL CLIMB EFFORT - TEMPO TO FINISH
WorkoutDescription: GOAL TODAY IS TO WARM UP WELL, GET INTO SOME TEMPO AND THEN HAMMER A TIME TRIAL EFFORT FOR 15 - 20 PLUS MINUTES - END THE DAY WITH SOME TEMPO SPIN - Warm up well today, anywhere from 15-30 minutes if outside - When ready, and have the space to maintain some intensity, roll into a steady pace for a few minutes, then tap the pedals a little faster into tempo, HR 150-160 for 5-6 minutes - And then GO for it, work a fast paced 15-20 minute effort, HR anywhere in the 160-175 range, power 250-290 plus watts - Focus more on the effort than power and HR - lay it all out there, then recover post effort - For the rest of the ride spin between tempo in the 140-150's and steady spin in the 130-140's HR.

Title: MAINTAINENCE - UPPER BODY FOCUSED
WorkoutDescription: WORK THESE FIRST 3 EXERCISES AS AS A CIRCUIT - 3 ROUNDS THEN MOVE ON GO FROM EXERCISE TO EXERCISE FAST, TAKE 1-2 MINUTES BETWEEN ROUNDS PLANK PUSH UPS WITH HANDLEBAR ON BALANCE BOARD - Get into a plank using a handlebar or something similar on a balance object such as a wood cylinder - hold for 30 seconds - DO 3 PUSH UPS AT THE 30 SECOND MARK, hold for an additional 30 seconds - FINISH WITH 3 PUSH UPS - IF NO EQUIPMENT FOR THIS, JUST DO IT ON THE FLOOR ON HANDS https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=b5HuGSSXIMM STAIRS - 3 FLIGHTS - Make sure you have firm foot placement, using one story, run the steps, 2 at a time if possible - down and repeat 2 more times PLANK PUSH UPS WITH HANDLEBAR ON BALANCE BOARD - Get into a plank using a handlebar or something similar on a balance object such as a wood cylinder - hold for 30 seconds - DO 3 PUSH UPS AT THE 30 SECOND MARK, hold for an additional 30 seconds - FINISH WITH 3 PUSH UPS - IF NO EQUIPMENT FOR THIS, JUST DO IT ON THE FLOOR ON HANDS BROAD JUMPS - Feet hip width, bend knees and jump with both feet as far as you can forward - immediately repeat once more for 2 jumps n a row - Take 20-30 sec and repeat 5 more times ---DO ALL THE ABOVE FOR 3 ROUNDS THEN MOVE ON TO THE EXERCISES BELOW--- WORK THESE NEXT EXERCISES ONE AT A TIME TURKISH GET UP - This can be done with a kettle bell or dumbbell, progress from laying on the ground to pressing the weight overhead - This is best described with a photo - Complete 1 on each side, alternate sides, or one side at a time. - 3 rounds https://images.app.goo.gl/qvLeS9xTUeXjM1kR6 SIDE PLANK DIPS - Start in a plank position on one side, stacking feet, resting on elbow, lifting hips as high as you can - Then lower the hip to the floor and lift back to the side plank - Repeat this 15 times on one side, alternate sides and skip rest for one round - 3 rounds BOAT POSE - While seated on the floor, legs together and hands on ground next to hips - Lift the legs in the air 45 degrees and hold for 10 seconds, then lift hands off the ground and reach hands to the outsides of the knees/arms straight and hold for 60 seconds - Repeat 2-3 times REVERSE PLANKS - Seated with legs together, ankles touching, and hands on floor outside of hips - Press into hands, straighten legs and let head drop back - Lift hips as high as you possible can and hold for 10-15 seconds - Release and then repeat 4 times HEEL RAISES - On a ledge on toes, lift and lower heels - 20 reps Chest press machine Shoulder press Bench rows machine Flys Lay pull down machine Lateral raise FINISH THE DAY WITH STRETCHES

Title: SPRINTS INTO TEMPO/SUB LT
WorkoutDescription: PUT IN A HARD EFFORT FOR 30-60 SECONDS AND THEN FOLLOW IT WITH EITHER TEMPO SPIN, OR A SUB LT EFFORT - Warm up as usual, checking bio feedback - Add more warm up if needed - When ready, Nuke it into a fast paced 30-60 second threshold effort, HR can climb into the 165-175 ranges - Power can be 350 plus watts -Then post effort, ease into either a tempo pace, in the 150-160 HR range, 250-270 watts range OR work a Sub LT effort in the 160-170 HR, 260-290 watts - Aim to work 5-7 minute efforts post sprint- Space these efforts by at least 10-15 min with steady fluid spin anywhere in the 130-140's - handful of efforts today, 4-6 - End the ride with one good tempo effort, 10-15 minutes
CoachComments: SPRINT ON FLATS, HILLS, TRAILS AND ROADS WHERE SAFE, THEN EITHER TEMPO OR SUB LT, DO WHAT YOUR FEELING - IF FEELING GOOD EXTEND THE EFFORTS

Title: FAST CADENCE EFFORTS - STEADY SPIN
WorkoutDescription: MIX IN SEATED 10-20 SEC FAST CADENCE EFFORTS TODAY FOLLOWED BY STEADY SPIN - Warm up into the 130-140HR ranges to check bio feedback today - if feeling great fatigue, add more warm up and work less efforts - Then choose sections of trail or road, shift into an easier gear, stay seated and spin with fast cadence - 95-115 RPM - 500-800 Watts for 10-20 seconds - After each effort and spin it steady in the 135-155HR ranges - Just toss a handful of spin efforts into the mix today - 4-6 efforts, and finish the ride steady spinning
CoachComments: KEEP IT SIMPLE, FEW CADENCE EFFORTS TODAY, STEADY FLOW BETWEEN

Title: HAMMER RIDE - FAST UP, FLOW ON THE DOWN
WorkoutDescription: WORK INTO ALL THE CLIMBS TODAY AND TRY TO MAINTAIN A SUB LT/LT PACE ON ALL OF THEM - ENJOY THE DOWNHILLS AND FLATS AND SPIN IT OUT - After a good warm up, target all the climbs today, easing into the efforts, letting HR rise into the 165-175 ranges - Power 290-320 plus ranges - Spinning seated and standing fluidly - Spin fluid and easier between hills, 130-140's HR - Keep it this simple, aim for 3-5 good hills each hour, or fewer longer climbs at least today
CoachComments: GO HAVE FUN - WORK ALL THE CLIMBS TODAY - WORK ALL OF THEM HARD - IF INDOORS PICK CLIMBS TO WORK HARD ON OR WORK THE WORKOUT ATTACHED

Title: TEMPO ON CLIMBS - HIGH RPM
WorkoutDescription: GOAL IS TO WORK IN A STEADY FLOW, WITH FEWER BREAKS - SPIN SMOOTH AND WITH A NATURAL, SLIGHTLY FASTER CADENCE - ON CLIMBS, HOLD TEMPO RANGES BUT KEEP IT THERE - Warm up into the 130's HR and check bio feedback as always, if feeling greater fatigue, higher PE, add more warm up - When feeling good, get into a steady fluid endurance pace today in the 140-150HR ranges - Keep breath deep and tap on the pedals and work a higher RPM than normal- On all climbs, tempo spin it, 150-160 HR range, as much speed and power but cap HR at 165 - WORK WITH A SLIGHTLY FASTER CADENCE WITH TEMPO, 90-100 RPM RANGE - Keep it this simple all day, with fewer breaks.

Title: TEMPO INTO SHORT RACE PACE EFFORTS
WorkoutDescription: STEADY SPIN IT WITH SOME SPEED INTO SHORT RACE PACE EFFORTS TODAY - KEEP LOTS OF EASIER SPIN IN THE MIX - Warm up as always checking how you feel, adding more warm up if needed - Then when ready, get into a steady fluid/tempo spin, 145-160 HR ranges, for 2-3 minutes or until feeling fluid - Once in a fluid pace, NUKE it into a fast race pace effort for 30-60 seconds, like you are trying to gap a rider ahead of you - HR can rise into the 150-160's, but focus on the effort more than HR - Fully recover after these little sessions today for 5-10 minutes spinning easy and fluid - Work a handful of these efforts, 5-10 efforts, group a few close together, space a few apart, depending on how you feel. - Anytime in the ride, add 5-10 minutes of tempo spin, 150-160HR
CoachComments: WORK IN SOME EFFORTS, PREP THE LEGS FOR THIS WEEKEND - ON THE BIKE FOR THIS WEEKEND

Title: SHORT SPIN - PREP
WorkoutDescription: KEEP IT EASY TODAY AND SPIN IN THE 135-155 RANGE FOR MOST OF THE SPIN - KEEP IT LIGHT ON THE PEDALS AND WORK WITH A NATURAL CADENCE - ADD A FEW VERY SHORT 6-10 SEC BURSTS TODAY AS WELL - Warm up and check to see how your feeling once you spin into the 140 range today. How is your breathing here? How do your legs feel? --- keep most of the spin in the 130-140 ranges but when your feeling it, add a few short 6-10 sec standing or seated bursts of speed working super hard with fast leg speed - Completely recover after each effort for 7-10 min and spin easy - only perform a few efforts (2-3) and then spin it home easy
CoachComments: FEW EFFORTS - MAINLY FLUID AND EASY

Title: REST DAY - YOGA STRETCHES
WorkoutDescription: TAKE TODAY COMPLETELY OFF - Stretch when you can and focus on stretching the hips STRETCHES - DOWNWARD DOG - http://www.yogajournal.com/pose/downward-facing-dog/ - Hold for 60 seconds HERO - All of these poses are great on this page - http://www.sensational-yoga-poses.com/virasana.html - Hold for 60 seconds PIGEON - http://www.yogajournal.com/article/yogapedia/master-sleeping-pigeon-pose-4-steps/ - Hold for 60 seconds DOWNWARD DOG (AGAIN) - http://www.yogajournal.com/pose/downward-facing-dog/ - Hold for 60 seconds INTENSE HAMSTRING STRETCH - Cross legs while standing, outside of feet touching - Then fold forward to touch toes - Go as far as you can and hold this for 20-30 seconds - Switch legs and repeat - Do each leg twice IT STRETCH - STANDING LEGS CROSSED - https://www.researchgate.net/figure/242017983_fig12_ITB-stretch-a-upright-standing-b-overhead-clasped-hands-and-c-diagonally-lowered Keep feet together for the IT stretch - Simply cross legs while standing, outside of feet touching, hands in the air and then lead to one side to stretch the IT band Hold each side for 30-60 seconds

Title: SPRINTS EARLY - SUB LT MID RIDE - TEMPO LATE
WorkoutDescription: GOAL IS TO WORK THREE DIFFERENT WAYS TODAY STARTING WITH EARLY RIDE SHORT SPRINTS, THEN INTO SUB THRESHOLD EFFORTS MID RIDE AND TEMPO SPIN TO END THE DAY - Warm up as usual in the 140's HR, check to see how your feeling, take more warm up if needed - Once warmed up and feeling fluid, early ride get into short 10-20 second sprints, can be on trail sections, on road to a sign or gaping a rider ahead - Don't worry about HR and power for these just Nuke hard efforts - Mid ride spin seated efforts, first into tempo for 5-7 minutes, 150-160HR, then into a threshold effort, 5 plus minutes, 165-175HR - 270-290 plus watts - Do 3-4 of these efforts an hour if outside - late ride seated tempo spin, 150-160HR, spin with as much speed and power as you have, just cap HR at 160 - Cool down to finish it out.
CoachComments: IF THE HILLS ARE SHORT, JUST WORK SHORT RAMPS UP TO THRESHOLD - ON LONGER CLIMBS FLOW BETWEEN EFFORTS AND STEADY SPIN

Title: LONG TEMPO EFFORTS

When warmed up and ready, choose sections of trail or roads, especially on the hill grades and climbs, and spin mainly seated into the 150-160HR ranges for duration s of 10-20 plus minutes - Power goal can be 250 - 270 PLUS watts, just keep HR under 165 - If you feel good and can work up to 30 min efforts, go for it - Easier, steady spin for between all efforts today, 130-140's HR - Work efforts on and off all day until speed and power drops - If speed or power doesn't drop, work these all day and have fun with it - Remember, push speed and power, keep breath deep and HR in line

Title: SUB LT SPIN EFFORTS

Ease into the 130 HR range and check your bio feedback - When you are feeling good, up your pace into tempo for 3-5 minutes, 150-160HR, then stay seated and spin with a faster cadence into the Sub LT range, 160-170 HR range - 265-290 plus watts - Try to hold that effort for at least 3-5 minutes, up to 10 minutes - Keep it as simple as that and work in 5-10 efforts today - Keep the rest of the day an easier/steady spin in the 130-140'sHR ranges

When warmed up and ready, choose sections of trail or roads, especially on the hill grades and climbs, and spin mainly seated into the 150-160HR ranges for duration s of 10-20 plus minutes - Power goal can be 250 - 270 PLUS watts, just keep HR under 165 - If you feel good and can work up to 30 min efforts, go for it - Easier, steady spin for between all efforts today, 130-140's HR - Work efforts on and off all day until speed and power drops - If speed or power doesn't drop, work these all day and have fun with it - Remember, push speed and power, keep breath deep and HR in line
CoachComments: ALL YOU NEED AFTER THIS PAST WEEKEND

Title: FORCE WORK - TEMPO
WorkoutDescription: JAM OUT FORCE EFFORTS TODAY FOR THE MAJORITY OF THE RIDE - SHIFT HARDER GEARS AND GRIND OUT EFFORTS - Warm up into the 130's HR, check how you feel - When ready, early ride, shift a gear or two harder (or use a single speed) and grind a few hills - Just get into the effort, can be shorter 30-60 seconds or longer 1-5 plus minute efforts - HR can rise into the 150's-160's, cadence 50-70 rpm but focus more on grinding an effort over power and HR - Work force efforts throughout the day with a few seated tempo spin efforts, HR into the 150-160HR range - Power goal can be 260-280 plus watt range for these efforts - Keep the spin between everything today steady and fun, 130-140's.
CoachComments: 60-90 MIN INSIDE - IF OUTDOORS DOESN'T NEED TO BE THIS PERFECT, FORCE FOCUSED RIDE, WORK THE LEGS AND CORE ON THE BIKE

Title: SPRINT/RACE PACE HOLDS
WorkoutDescription: GOAL TODAY IS TO PICK SECTIONS OF TRAIL AND ROAD, NUKE IT INTO AN EFFORT AND THEN HOLD THAT PACE FOR 5-10 MIN - Warm up as always into the 140's checking how you feel - if more warm up is needed, take it - Then choose sections of trail, road, Strava segment, and nuke it, standing seated all out sprint first few seconds, then sustain this fast effort for 5-10 minutes - FOCUS MORE ON SUSTAINING A FAST EFFORT THAN ON POWER OR HR - HR can elevate into the 160-175 ranges, power 250-320 plus watts - but again, focus on a fast effort like gaping a rider, fast leg speed - Spin anywhere between 130-150HR between efforts - 4-7 good efforts today - End the ride with 1-2 all out 10-15 second sprints
CoachComments: KEEP TODAY SIMPLE, HIT IT HARD, THEN FAST PACE IT - GOOD DAY FOR A GROUP
AthleteComments: *07/29/2023 Abigail Snyder: Knee hurt to start, so took a nice long warmup before the first effort. Did most of the ride on trails, then did my last effort around a greenway loop with a small skills park in the middle.* *07/29/2023 Abigail Snyder: Garmin wanted to give me a new ftp (lower) of 261... for whatever that's worth.*

Title: SUB LT SPIN EFFORTS
WorkoutDescription: WORK WITH A FASTER CADENCE SEATED, WHILE REACHING THE TARGETED HR RANGES TODAY - TRY TO WORK WITH LESS FORCE AND MORE SPIN - take your time warming up as always. Ease into the 130 HR range and check your bio feedback - When you are feeling good, up your pace into tempo for 3-5 minutes, 150-160HR, then stay seated and spin with a faster cadence into the Sub LT range, 160-170 HR range - 270-290 plus watts - Try to hold that effort for at least 3-5 minutes, up to 10 minutes - Keep it as simple as that and work in 5-10 efforts today - Keep the rest of the day an easier/steady spin in the 130-140'sHR ranges
CoachComments: PICK SHORT HILLS AND SPIN THEM SEATED, SUB LT RANGES - IF PE IS HIGH TODAY, LEGS HURT, JUST BACK OFF THE EFFORTS AND SPIN IT OUT - NO NEED FOR A TON OF EFFORTS EITHER

Title: TEMPO INTO SHORT RACE PACE EFFORTS
WorkoutDescription: STEADY SPIN IT WITH SOME SPEED INTO SHORT RACE PACE EFFORTS TODAY - KEEP LOTS OF EASIER SPIN IN THE MIX - Warm up as always checking how you feel, adding more warm up if needed - Then when ready, get into a steady fluid/tempo spin, 145-160 HR ranges, for 2-3 minutes or until feeling fluid - Once in a fluid pace, NUKE it into a fast race pace effort for 30-60 seconds, like you are trying to gap a rider ahead of you - HR can rise into the 150-160's, but focus on the effort more than HR - Fully recover after these little sessions today for 5-10 minutes spinning easy and fluid - Work a handful of these efforts, 5-10 efforts, group a few close together, space a few apart, depending on how you feel. - Anytime in the ride, add 5-10 minutes of tempo spin, 150-160HR
CoachComments: WORK IN SOME EFFORTS, PREP THE LEGS FOR THIS WEEKEND - ON THE BIKE FOR THIS WEEKEND

Title: SHORT SPIN - PREP
WorkoutDescription: KEEP IT EASY TODAY AND SPIN IN THE 135-155 RANGE FOR MOST OF THE SPIN - KEEP IT LIGHT ON THE PEDALS AND WORK WITH A NATURAL CADENCE - ADD A FEW VERY SHORT 6-10 SEC BURSTS TODAY AS WELL - Warm up and check to see how your feeling once you spin into the 140 range today. How is your breathing here? How do your legs feel? --- keep most of the spin in the 130-140 ranges but when your feeling it, add a few short 6-10 sec standing or seated bursts of speed working super hard with fast leg speed - Completely recover after each effort for 7-10 min and spin easy - only perform a few efforts (2-3) and then spin it home easy
CoachComments: FEW EFFORTS - MAINLY FLUID AND EASY

Title: TEMPO ON CLIMBS - HIGH RPM
WorkoutDescription: GOAL IS TO WORK IN A STEADY FLOW, WITH FEWER BREAKS - SPIN SMOOTH AND WITH A NATURAL, SLIGHTLY FASTER CADENCE - ON CLIMBS, HOLD TEMPO RANGES BUT KEEP IT THERE - Warm up into the 130's HR and check bio feedback as always, if feeling greater fatigue, higher PE, add more warm up - When feeling good, get into a steady fluid endurance pace today in the 140-150HR ranges - Keep breath deep and tap on the pedals and work a higher RPM than normal- On all climbs, tempo spin it, 150-160 HR range, as much speed and power but cap HR at 165 - WORK WITH A SLIGHTLY FASTER CADENCE WITH TEMPO, 90-100 RPM RANGE - Keep it this simple all day, with fewer breaks.

Title: MID RIDE THRESHOLD - CAPPED WITH TEMPO EFFORTS
WorkoutDescription: WORK INTO SHORT AND LONG THRESHOLD EFFORTS TODAY MID RIDE - KEEP IT SIMPLE - CAP THE DAY WITH TEMPO EFFORTS - take your time warming up as always. Ease into the 140 HR range and check your bio feedback - If you have any fatigue today while warming up, add more warm up spin before efforts - To start the day, spin into tempo efforts, one longer 10 plus minute or shorter efforts if outside, HR 150-160, power 270 plus watts - Steady spin for a little then nuke some harder threshold efforts mid ride - Choose stretches of road or trail for an effort, seated and standing, spin it into threshold ranges, 165-175 HR range - Short or longer efforts, from a minute to 5-10 plus minutes - Power goals can be 290-320 plus watts for efforts - End of ride, work more tempo, short and long efforts or one longer effort 10 plus minutes
CoachComments: RAMP UP TO SOME THRESHOLD EFFORTS TODAY MID RIDE - JUST WORK THE EFFORT EVEN IF PE IS HIGH AND HR IS ON THE LOWER END!

Title: FAST CADENCE - TEMPO
WorkoutDescription: MIX IN SEATED 10-20 SEC FAST CADENCE EFFORTS TODAY FOLLOWED BY TEMPO PACE AND STEADY SPIN - Warm up into the 130-140 HR ranges to check bio feedback today - if feeling great fatigue, add more warm up and work less efforts - Then choose sections of trail or road, shift into an easier gear, stay seated and spin with fast cadence - 95-115 RPM - 500-700 Watts for 10-20 seconds, 10-20 sec easy, then on again for a few rounds - After the fast cadence, spin fluid tempo efforts, 150-160HR for 10 plus min efforts - add in steady spin between efforts when needed, have fun with it.
CoachComments: GET THE LEGS SPINNING FAST, RIGHT INTO TEMPO - KEEP IT SIMPLE AND FUN

Title: JUMPS INTO SUB LT - TEMPO TO END
WorkoutDescription: WORK ROUNDS OF CONTINUOUS SEATED TO STANDING JUMPS - THESE CAN BE WORKED ON HILLS OR FLATS, INTO A SUB LT SPIN EFFORT - Warm up as usual assessing how you feel, checking bio feedback in the 130-140 HR ranges - Once warmed up and ready, steady spin anywhere into the 140-160 HR ranges, so that your working with a steady speed - Start seated and Nuke it into a standing effort for a 7-10 seconds, 600-900 watts - then sit for 20-30 seconds and immediately repeat - Work 5-10 jumps - After the jumps, spin sub LT ranges for an additional 5-10 minutes, 160-170HR, 260-280 plus watts - Spin easy between these rounds of efforts , 130-140's - On hills or flats or both - Try to work 2-3 rounds of these efforts today and have fun with it - End of ride work a few tempo efforts into the mix, 150-160 HR 250-270 watts
CoachComments: JUST SOME JUMPS TO FIRE UP THE LEGS, PLENTY OF STEADY/EASIER SPIN TODAY

Easy rolled it back to the car because I was out of water and dying… drank 2.5 bottles, then headed back out to try and do the tempo set. Felt like I worked a long time before Hr would rise… and power was questionable at best. So hot & so tired.*

Title: STOMP/FORCE THEN SPIN
WorkoutDescription: START EFFORTS WITH BIG GEARS, ON STEEPS, ETC, GRINDING THE FIRST 10-15 SECONDS, THEN SIT, SHIFT AND SPIN FAST LEGS TO FINISH - STEADY TEMPO BETWEEN - After warm up, and feeling fluid, seek out hills and work into efforts starting with a slower cadence, harder gears and NUKE it for the first 10-15 seconds - Could come to a slow roll into a hill with big gears and start from there, then after the initial grind, sit and shift up a gear easier, spinning with a fast and fluid cadence while maintaining Sub LT HR in the 160-170 ranges, for an additional 3-5 minutes - power 270-300 watt ranges - Work in 4-6 of these efforts today - Between efforts spin steady/ tempo ranges, anywhere in the 140-160 HR, fluid - End of ride, 1-2 form sprints, big gears, seated fast spin 10 seconds
CoachComments: GRIND OUT THE START OF EFFORTS, THEN SIT AND SPIN IT OUT - MIX OF FORCE AND SPIN, GOOD FUNCTIONAL POWER BUILDERS

Title: FORCE EARLY - MODERATE/FAST PACE EFFORTS TO END
WorkoutDescription: WORK INTO HILLS AND GRIND OUT SEATED/STANDING FORCE EFFORTS EARLY RIDE, THEN FOCUS ON FAST PACED EFFORT IN THE SUB LT/LT RANGE TO END - Warm up into the 130's HR, check how you feel - When ready, early ride, shift a gear or two harder (or use a single speed) Work both standing and seated and grind a few hills - Seek out any incline or hill, can be shorter 30-60 seconds or longer 1-3 plus minute efforts - HR can rise into the 150-160's, cadence 50-70 rpm - power goal 300-500 watts - Work a handful of force efforts first half of the ride, 4-8 efforts - Second half of the ride get into race pace efforts, aim for longer 5-10 minute sustained efforts - HR can rise anywhere in the 155-170 HR range, Power goal anywhere from 270-330 watts - Focus more on a fast paced effort and bike handling than the numbers but use the numbers to guide you - Keep plenty of easier spin between efforts today
CoachComments: A COMBO OF FORCE AND SPEED WORK AT THE END, PICK A FUN ROUTE, WORK THE TERRAIN AS BEST YOU CAN, DOESN'T NEED TO BE PERFECT AND HAVE FUN WITH IT

Title: STOMP/FORCE THEN SPIN
WorkoutDescription: START EFFORTS WITH BIG GEARS, ON STEEPS, ETC, GRINDING THE FIRST 10-15 SECONDS, THEN SIT, SHIFT AND SPIN FAST LEGS TO FINISH - STEADY TEMPO BETWEEN - After warm up, and feeling fluid, seek out hills and work into efforts starting with a slower cadence, harder gears and NUKE it for the first 10-15 seconds - Could come to a slow roll into a hill with big gears and start from there, then after the initial grind, sit and shift up a gear easier, spinning with a fast and fluid cadence while maintaining Sub LT HR in the 160-170 ranges, for an additional 3-5 minutes - power 260-290 watt ranges - Work in 4-6 of these efforts today - Between efforts spin steady/ tempo ranges, anywhere in the 140-160 HR, fluid - End of ride, 1-2 form sprints, big gears, seated fast spin 10 seconds
CoachComments: GRIND OUT THE START OF EFFORTS, THEN SIT AND SPIN IT OUT - MIX OF FORCE AND SPIN, GOOD FUNCTIONAL POWER BUILDERS

I’m blaming the tire choice… and all the stress from this week/life.* *09/12/2023 Abigail Snyder: Also power meter seems to be cutting in and out... working with Quarq customer service on it...*

Title: TEMPO ON CLIMBS - HIGH RPM
WorkoutDescription: GOAL IS TO WORK IN A STEADY FLOW, WITH FEWER BREAKS - SPIN SMOOTH AND WITH A NATURAL, SLIGHTLY FASTER CADENCE - ON CLIMBS, HOLD TEMPO RANGES BUT KEEP IT THERE - Warm up into the 130's HR and check bio feedback as always, if feeling greater fatigue, higher PE, add more warm up - When feeling good, get into a steady fluid endurance pace today in the 140-155HR ranges - Keep breath deep and tap on the pedals and work a higher RPM than normal- On all climbs, tempo spin it, 150-160 HR range, as much speed and power but cap HR at 165 - WORK WITH A SLIGHTLY FASTER CADENCE WITH TEMPO, 90-100 RPM RANGE - Keep it this simple all day, with fewer breaks.
CoachComments: SHORT TEMPO - JUST LIKE TUESDAY, BUT WORK A HIGHER RPM TODAY, JUST BY 5-7 RPMS

Title: SPRINT/RACE PACE HOLDS
WorkoutDescription: GOAL TODAY IS TO PICK SECTIONS OF TRAIL AND ROAD, NUKE IT INTO AN EFFORT AND THEN HOLD THAT PACE FOR 5-10 MIN - Warm up as always into the 140's checking how you feel - if more warm up is needed, take it - Then choose sections of trail, road, Strava segment, and nuke it, standing seated all out sprint first few seconds, then sustain this fast effort for 5-10 minutes - FOCUS MORE ON SUSTAINING A FAST EFFORT THAN ON POWER OR HR - HR can elevate into the 160-175 ranges, power 250-320 plus watts - but again, focus on a fast effort like gaping a rider, fast leg speed - Spin anywhere between 130-150HR between efforts - 4-7 good efforts today - End the ride with 1-2 all out 10-15 second sprints
CoachComments: KEEP TODAY SIMPLE, HIT IT HARD, THEN FAST PACE IT - GOOD DAY FOR A GROUP **There's a CX race here in town, so my plan is to get about 2:30:00 in solo, then ride over to the CX race with my SS & do the SS race (0:45:00), then ride home. So my ride will be split between MTB and CX, but should accomplish the goal for today & get total time in, even if with some breaks.

Title: SHORT SUB LT SPIN EFFORTS
WorkoutDescription: WORK WITH A FASTER CADENCE SEATED, WHILE REACHING THE TARGETED HR RANGES TODAY - TRY TO WORK WITH LESS FORCE AND MORE SPIN - take your time warming up as always. Ease into the 130 HR range and check your bio feedback - When you are feeling good, up your pace into tempo for 3-5 minutes, 150-160HR, then stay seated and spin with a faster cadence into the Sub LT range, 160-170 HR range - 270-290 plus watts - Try to hold that effort for at least 3-5 minutes, KEEP IT TO SHORTER EFFORTS TODAY - Keep it as simple as that and work in 5-10 efforts today - Keep the rest of the day an easier/steady spin in the 130-140'sHR ranges
CoachComments: FOCUS ON SHORTER EFFORTS TODAY, LIKE 2-3 MINUTES, WITH PLENTY OF EASIER SPIN BETWEEN

Title: LONG TEMPO EFFORTS
WorkoutDescription: FOCUS ON STEADY SPIN IN THE 150-160 RANGE FOR 20-30 MINUTE PERIODS - STEADY EASIER SPINNING BETWEEN EFFORTS - Warm up and ride into the 130 ranges, add a few jumps, get the system going - Check your bio feedback here. When warmed up and ready, choose sections of trail or roads, especially on the hill grades and climbs, and spin mainly seated into the 150-160HR ranges for duration s of 10-20 plus minutes - Power goal can be 250 - 270 PLUS watts, just keep HR under 165 - If you feel good and can work up to 30 min efforts, go for it - Easier, steady spin for between all efforts today, 130-140's HR - Work efforts on and off all day until speed and power drops - If speed or power doesn't drop, work these all day and have fun with it - Remember, push speed and power, keep breath deep and HR in line
CoachComments: KEEP IT TO TEMPO TODAY - YOU CAN ADD ONE OR TWO DIGS BUT KEEP IT SIMPLE.
AthleteComments: *10/19/2023 Abigail Snyder: Held tempo up the climb, then chilled coming down.*

Title: SPRINT/RACE PACE HOLDS
WorkoutDescription: GOAL TODAY IS TO PICK SECTIONS OF TRAIL AND ROAD, NUKE IT INTO AN EFFORT AND THEN HOLD THAT PACE FOR 5-10 MIN - Warm up as always into the 130's HR checking how you feel - if more warm up is needed, take it - Then choose sections of trail, road, Strava segment, and nuke it, standing seated all out sprint first few seconds, then sustain this fast effort for 5-10 minutes - FOCUS MORE ON SUSTAINING A FAST EFFORT THAN ON POWER OR HR - HR can elevate into the 160-175 ranges, power 250-320 plus watts - but again, focus on a fast effort like gaping a rider, fast leg speed - Spin anywhere between 130-150HR between efforts - 4-7 good efforts today - End the ride with 1-2 all out 10-15 second sprints
CoachComments: KEEP TODAY SIMPLE, HIT IT HARD, THEN FAST PACE IT - GOOD DAY FOR A GROUP
AthleteComments: *10/21/2023 Abigail Snyder: RPE was high even if HR wasn't.*

Title: STEADY FLUID SPIN
WorkoutDescription: WORK A STEADY PACE IN THE 140-155 RANGES MAINLY WITH FEW BREAKS - FOCUS ON WORKING SMOOTH AND WITH A NATURAL CADENCE - Warm up and ride into the 120-130HR ranges. Check your bio feedback here. Where is your breath? Where is your PE? How do your legs feel? If you feel good fatigue, add more warm up and back off the ranges for the day- If all is feeling good then spin in the 140-155 HR range for most of the ride today - Add easier spin breaks when needed

Title: SUB LT SPIN EFFORTS
WorkoutDescription: WORK WITH A FASTER CADENCE SEATED, WHILE REACHING THE TARGETED HR RANGES TODAY - TRY TO WORK WITH LESS FORCE AND MORE SPIN - take your time warming up as always. Ease into the 130 HR range and check your bio feedback - When you are feeling good, up your pace into tempo for 3-5 minutes, 150-160HR, then stay seated and spin with a faster cadence into the Sub LT range, 160-170 HR range - 270-290 plus watts - Try to hold that effort for at least 3-5 minutes, up to 10 minutes - Keep it as simple as that and work in 5-10 efforts today - Keep the rest of the day an easier/steady spin in the 130-140'sHR ranges
CoachComments: PICK SHORT HILLS AND SPIN THEM SEATED, SUB LT RANGES - IF PE IS HIGH TODAY, LEGS HURT, JUST BACK OFF THE EFFORTS AND SPIN IT OUT - NO NEED FOR A TON OF EFFORTS EITHER

Title: THRESHOLD EFFORTS - HAMMER RIDE
WorkoutDescription: WORK INTO SHORT AND LONG THRESHOLD EFFORTS TODAY - KEEP IT SIMPLE AND WORK HARD EFFORTS ALL DAY - take your time warming up as always. Ease into the 130 HR range and check your bio feedback - If you have any fatigue today while warming up, add more warm up spin before efforts - Then choose stretches of road or trail for an effort, stay seated, spin into tempo ranges first, 150-160HR range for 3-4 minutes, then up it into threshold, 165-175 HR range - Try to hold that effort for at least 4-5 minutes at times and at times shorter 1-2 min efforts are good - if feeling good, hold it up to 10 minutes - Power goals can be 290-320 plus watts for efforts - Space efforts today with steady spin in the 130's-140's HR and aim to get in 4-6 good efforts - End of ride, 1-2 big gear form sprints, big ring super fast cadence seated on a flat or slight downgrade for 10-15 seconds
CoachComments: GO HAMMER - WORK ALL THE CLIMBS TODAY - TIME TO GET THE LEGS FIRED UP - RAMP INTO EFFORTS TOO - IF THEY FEEL DEAD, THEN DO A FEW EFFORTS, BACK OFF MOST OF THE RIDE
AthleteComments: *10/29/2023 Abigail Snyder: Felt good today. TT-style format, so kind of like racing myself. Rode well technically (aside from blowing through some loose corners I didn’t know were there), and felt good pedaling. Finally starting to adapt to the hardtail again.*

Title: SHORT SPIN - PREP
WorkoutDescription: KEEP IT EASY TODAY AND SPIN IN THE 135-155 RANGE FOR MOST OF THE SPIN - KEEP IT LIGHT ON THE PEDALS AND WORK WITH A NATURAL CADENCE - ADD A FEW VERY SHORT 6-10 SEC BURSTS TODAY AS WELL - Warm up and check to see how your feeling once you spin into the 140 range today. How is your breathing here? How do your legs feel? --- keep most of the spin in the 130-140 ranges but when your feeling it, add a few short 6-10 sec standing or seated bursts of speed working super hard with fast leg speed - Completely recover after each effort for 7-10 min and spin easy - only perform a few efforts (2-3) and then spin it home easy

Title: LONG TEMPO INTO SUB-LT SPIKES
WorkoutDescription: EASE INTO LONGER SEATED TEMPO EFFORTS TODAY - FINISH EACH TEMPO EFFORT WITH A FEW MINUTES OF SUB THRESHOLD PACE WORK - Warm up as usual, checking bio feedback - Add more warm up if needed - When ready, pick up speed and power and ease into a tempo pace effort in the 150-160 HR range - Power goal can be 255-270 plus watts - Aim for longer 7-10 min, up to 20 min efforts - At the end of the tempo effort, up the pace into the sub-threshold HR and power ranges, HR can rise into the 160-170 range, power can be 290 plus watts - Space these efforts by at least 10-15 min with steady fluid spin anywhere in the 130-140's - Aim for 2-3 solid, longer efforts here today
CoachComments: SAVE SOME FOR THE THRESHOLD EFFORT AT THE END, SO CUT THE TEMPO SHORT IF NEEDED - OUTSIDE DOESN'T NEED TO BE PERFECT, AT LEAST A FEW HARD EFFORTS AT THE END OF TEMPO PACES TODAY

Should be good to go once everything normalizes to training again haha.*

Title: PYRAMID INCREASES - STEADY SPIN
WorkoutDescription: WORK THROUGH ALL THE RANGES FROM LOW TO HIGH TODAY, SPACED WITH GENERAL ENDURANCE SPIN - Warm up as always until your feeling fluid - Always check PE and if high, add more warm up - Then when ready and likely on a longer climb, ease into temp[o ranges, HR - 150-160 range, hold this for 5-10 minutes - Push power but keep HR in line - Then up the intensity into SUB LT ranges, 160-170HR for a 3-5 minute effort - Push power here, power goal can be 250-270 plus watts - Then cap the effort with a 1-3 minute threshold effort, HR 165-175 power goal is 310 plus watts - Recover for 5-10 minutes easy and steady spin anywhere in the 140-160 HR range between these efforts - 3-5 of these sets today would be ideal.
CoachComments: WORK ALL RANGES, RAMP IT UP ON THE CLIMBS, BUILDS GOOD BASE - IF OUTDOORS AND ON SHORT HILLS JUST RAMP UP IN DIFFERENT ZONES ON EACH CLIMB
AthleteComments: *11/28/2023 Abigail Snyder: If I do the longer ride Friday, might do this Sunday to give myself the rest day? We'll see how I feel.* *12/03/2023 Abigail Snyder: Felt ok. But also like I was dying during the harder efforts. Barely got it into threshold, even though I felt like i was working as hard as I could.*

Title: SEATED TO STANDING FORCE INTO TEMPO
WorkoutDescription: GET INTO SEATED FORCE EFFORTS ON CLIMBS, FINISHING THE EFFORT STANDING - WORK SOME TEMPO BETWEEN A FEW EFFORTS - Warm up into the 130's HR, check how you feel - When ready, on a climb, shift a gear or two harder (or use a single speed) remain seated and grind a 20-30 second effort, then stand and continue that effort for another 20-30 seconds - Efforts can be shorter 30-60 seconds or longer 2-5 plus minute efforts, just work the seated to standing theme - HR can rise into the 160's-170's, Power 400-500 watt range - cadence 50-70 rpm but focus more on grinding an effort - Sit and spin into tempo ranges, 150-160HR between a few efforts today, otherwise spin easier, 140's, to recover.
CoachComments: WORK IN TEMPO WHENEVER YOUR GOING UP, KEEP FLUID LEGS - LONG EFFORTS ARE OK - IF YOU SHUTTLE, THEN HAVE FUN!
AthleteComments: *12/04/2023 Abigail Snyder: Didn’t shuttle. Had fun.*

Title: TEMPO ON CLIMBS/FEW SPRINTS TO END
WorkoutDescription: GOAL IS TO WORK IN A STEADY FLOW, HR IN THE 150-160 RANGES, WITH FEWER BREAKS - SPIN SMOOTH AND WITH A NATURAL, SLIGHTLY FASTER CADENCE - ON CLIMBS, HOLD TEMPO RANGES BUT KEEP IT THERE - Warm up into the 140's HR and check bio feedback as always, if feeling greater fatigue, higher PE, add more warm up - When feeling good, get into a steady fluid endurance pace today in the 140-155HR ranges - Keep breath deep and tap on the pedals - On all climbs, tempo spin it, 150-160 HR range, as much speed and power but cap HR at 165 - Keep it this simple all day, with fewer breaks. - END OF RIDE, WORK IN 2-3 30-40 SECOND SPRINTS, RAMPING UP TO ALL OUT IN THE LAST 10 SECONDS OF THE SPRINT - If outdoors spring in safe places!
CoachComments: GET THE LEGS SPINNING FLUID, FEW SPRINTS - KEEP IT SIMPLE TODAY

Title: FORCE WORK - TEMPO
WorkoutDescription: JAM OUT FORCE EFFORTS TODAY FOR THE MAJORITY OF THE RIDE - SHIFT HARDER GEARS AND GRIND OUT EFFORTS - Warm up into the 130's HR, check how you feel - When ready, early ride, shift a gear or two harder (or use a single speed) and grind a few hills - Just get into the effort, can be shorter 30-60 seconds or longer 1-5 plus minute efforts - HR can rise into the 160's-170's, cadence 50-70 rpm but focus more on grinding an effort over power and HR - Work force efforts throughout the day with a few seated tempo spin efforts, HR into the 150-160HR range - Power goal can be 250-270 plus watt range for these efforts - Keep the spin between everything today steady and fun, 130-140's.
CoachComments: 60-90 MIN INSIDE - IF OUTDOORS DOESN'T NEED TO BE THIS PERFECT, ITS A SINGLE SPEED OR FORCE FOCUSED WEEK, WORK THE LEGS AND CORE ON THE BIKE

Title: FORCE EARLY - FAST CADENCE MID RIDE - LONG TEMPO LATE
WorkoutDescription: SHIFT A GEAR OR TWO HARDER EARLY RIDE AND WORK IN SHORT AND LONG FORCE EFFORTS, SEATED AND STANDING - MID RIDE WORK IN SHORT FAST CADENCE EFFORTS - LONG TEMPO EFFORT LATE RIDE - Warm up into the 130's HR, check how you feel - When ready early ride, on a climb, shift a gear or two harder (or use a single speed) work seated and standing and grind effort. - Efforts can be shorter 20-30 seconds or longer 2-5 plus minute efforts, just work the seated to standing theme - HR can rise into the 150's-160's, Power 300-500 watt range - cadence 50-70 rpm but focus more on grinding an effort - MID ride toss in 4-6, 10-20 sec fast cadence efforts, 90 plus RPMs - Late ride work in one longer tempo effort, HR in the 150-160 range steady - Keep it 130-140's HR between all. Have fun.
CoachComments: 60-90 MIN INSIDE - IF OUTDOORS DOESN'T NEED TO BE THIS PERFECT, JUST WORK FORCE, HILLS, CADENCE, SOME TEMPO - THEME FOR THE DAY

Title: LONG TEMPO INTO SUB LT
WorkoutDescription: EASE INTO LONGER SEATED TEMPO EFFORTS TODAY - FINISH EACH TEMPO EFFORT WITH A SUB THRESHOLD PACE EFFORT - Warm up as usual, checking bio feedback - Add more warm up if needed - When ready, pick up speed and power and ease into a tempo pace effort in the 150-160 HR range - Power goal can be 250-270 plus watts - Aim for longer 7-10 min, up to 20 min efforts - At the end of the tempo effort, up the pace/and cadence into the sub threshold HR and power ranges, anywhere from 1-5 minutes - HR can rise into the 160-170 range, power can be 280 plus watts - Space these efforts by at least 10-15 min with steady fluid spin anywhere in the 130-140's HR - Aim for 2-3 solid, longer efforts here today
CoachComments: TEMPO, SUB THRESHOLD - CUT THE TEMPO SHORT IF NEEDED TO GET IN AT LEAST A MIN OF THE HIGHER END EFFORT

Title: LONG TEMPO - HIGH RPM - ON CLIMBS
WorkoutDescription: FOCUS ON STEADY SPIN IN THE 150-160 RANGE FOR 20-30 MINUTE PERIODS - STEADY EASIER SPINNING BETWEEN EFFORTS - SPIN SMOOTH AND WITH A NATURAL, SLIGHTLY FASTER CADENCE - Warm up and ride into the 130 ranges, add a few jumps, get the system going - Check your bio feedback here. When warmed up and ready, choose sections of trail or roads, especially on the hill grades and climbs, and spin mainly seated into the 150-160HR ranges for duration s of 10-20 plus minutes - Work with a slightly faster cadence today, 3-5 rpm faster than normal - Power goal can be 250 - 270 watts, just keep HR under 165 - If you feel good and can work up to 30 min efforts, go for it - Easier, steady spin for between all efforts today, 130-140's HR - Work efforts on and off all day until speed and power drops - If speed or power doesn't drop, work these all day and have fun with it - Remember, push speed and power, keep breath deep and HR in line
CoachComments: INDOORS OR OUT, GOAL IS TO WORK THIS RANGE ALL DAY, BE FLUID, HAVE FUN, KEEP IT SIMPLE TODAY - INDOOR GOAL IS 60-90 MIN
